# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithWarrior1SleepWithSamayra
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Samayra had a bit to drink, but Sarah could see it hadn't been so much as to make this wrong."
    new "Samayra had a bit to drink, but Sarah could see it hadn't been so much as to make this wrong."

    old "And she couldn't deny that it was fun to see the girl take some initiative."
    new "And she couldn't deny that it was fun to see the girl take some initiative."

    old "Before long, the two found themselves back in Samayra's tent."
    new "Before long, the two found themselves back in Samayra's tent."

    old "It wasn't too impressive, given she was not a soldier and no longer a royal, Samayra didn't have much to her name."
    new "It wasn't too impressive, given she was not a soldier and no longer a royal, Samayra didn't have much to her name."

    old "Officially, she was only Sarah's slave or servant, though Sarah didn't treat her as such."
    new "Officially, she was only Sarah's slave or servant, though Sarah didn't treat her as such."

    old "Sarah fell down into some of the cushions that had been put on on the floor."
    new "Sarah fell down into some of the cushions that had been put on on the floor."

    old "Leaning back, she took in Samayra's body as the former princess began to slowly move her hips from side to side."
    new "Leaning back, she took in Samayra's body as the former princess began to slowly move her hips from side to side."

    old "She saw the girl throw back her head, softly shake it to a tune only she seemed to hear."
    new "She saw the girl throw back her head, softly shake it to a tune only she seemed to hear."

    old "I didn't know you were a dancer."
    new "I didn't know you were a dancer."

    old "Samayra softly laughed."
    new "Samayra softly laughed."

    old "There's a lot you don't know about me."
    new "There's a lot you don't know about me."

    old "Ooh really?"
    new "Ooh really?"

    old "Sarah couldn't help but be entertained by her behavior."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but be entertained by her behavior."

    old "Tell me, did you ever drink before?"
    new "Tell me, did you ever drink before?"

    old "Samayra, her face flushed, eagerly nodded."
    new "Samayra, her face flushed, eagerly nodded."

    old "Two...two cups, father always said. No more. Not lady like. But I'm free now..."
    new "Two...two cups, father always said. No more. Not lady like. But I'm free now..."

    old "So I drank..."
    new "So I drank..."

    old "Samayra threw up three fingers."
    new "Samayra threw up three fingers."

    old "That many."
    new "That many."

    old "You do know that mercenaries and soldiers lace their wine with harsher stuff, right?"
    new "You do know that mercenaries and soldiers lace their wine with harsher stuff, right?"

    old "Because they like the kick but can't afford the good stuff."
    new "Because they like the kick but can't afford the good stuff."

    old "Samayra threw out her hands and did a surprisingly graceful pirouette."
    new "Samayra threw out her hands and did a surprisingly graceful pirouette."

    old "I...did not know that."
    new "I...did not know that."

    old "She had a wide smile on her face as she said it."
    new "She had a wide smile on her face as she said it."

    old "Sarah watched on as Samayra continued to slowly sway her hips from side to side."
    new "Sarah watched on as Samayra continued to slowly sway her hips from side to side."

    old "You know, I used to take dancing classes too."
    new "You know, I used to take dancing classes too."

    old "Yeah. Back in Rosanna, before...well all of that happened."
    new "Yeah. Back in Rosanna, before...well all of that happened."

    old "I guess despite everything, some things are the same no matter where you go in the world."
    new "I guess despite everything, some things are the same no matter where you go in the world."

    old "Samayra threw our her arms and did another spin, this time she slightly stumbled but quickly recovered."
    new "Samayra threw our her arms and did another spin, this time she slightly stumbled but quickly recovered."

    old "Were you any good?"
    new "Were you any good?"

    old "Maybe. Some girls were better, but I did well enough to not embarrass myself."
    new "Maybe. Some girls were better, but I did well enough to not embarrass myself."

    old "I did always like to dance."
    new "I did always like to dance."

    old "Sarah looked away as she recalled a memory."
    new "Sarah looked away as she recalled a memory."

    old "My father...I'd show him whenever I had learned a new routine and he'd always stop doing whatever it was."
    new "My father...I'd show him whenever I had learned a new routine and he'd always stop doing whatever it was."

    old "He liked to say that my mother would have been proud, they said she could dance like no other."
    new "He liked to say that my mother would have been proud, they said she could dance like no other."

    old "Did she teach you?"
    new "Did she teach you?"

    old "My mother died before I started taking my lessons..."
    new "My mother died before I started taking my lessons..."

    old "Samayra suddenly stopped."
    new "Samayra suddenly stopped."

    old "Sarah...I'm sorry."
    new "Sarah...I'm sorry."

    old "Forget I said anything. It's been a long time. Whatever pain was there is long gone."
    new "Forget I said anything. It's been a long time. Whatever pain was there is long gone."

    old "Scars remained, though Sarah kept that to herself."
    new "Scars remained, though Sarah kept that to herself."

    old "Samayra walked up closer to Sarah."
    new "Samayra walked up closer to Sarah."

    old "You know, you're pretty tough, but it's ok to cry sometimes. I do it."
    new "You know, you're pretty tough, but it's ok to cry sometimes. I do it."

    old "Sarah smiled as she watched Samayra kneel down next to her."
    new "Sarah smiled as she watched Samayra kneel down next to her."

    old "There was a kindness in her face that seemed undulled, no matter her circumstances."
    new "There was a kindness in her face that seemed undulled, no matter her circumstances."

    old "Did you cry when Bagrad fell?"
    new "Did you cry when Bagrad fell?"

    old "Samayra softly nodded."
    new "Samayra softly nodded."

    old "I did...but life goes on. And now I got to meet you."
    new "I did...but life goes on. And now I got to meet you."

    old "Looking into her eyes, Sarah felt her own eyes begin to sting. Tears, so often held back, near the surface."
    new "Looking into her eyes, Sarah felt her own eyes begin to sting. Tears, so often held back, near the surface."

    old "But it was me..."
    new "But it was me..."

    old "Me and all these others did that to you. To your family."
    new "Me and all these others did that to you. To your family."

    old "Don't you hate me for that?"
    new "Don't you hate me for that?"

    old "Samayra suddenly leaned down. She softly pressed her lips up against Sarah's."
    new "Samayra suddenly leaned down. She softly pressed her lips up against Sarah's."

    old "Sarah could taste something sweet on her lips, she wonderd if it was the wine or something else."
    new "Sarah could taste something sweet on her lips, she wonderd if it was the wine or something else."

    old "She watched Samayra lean back again."
    new "She watched Samayra lean back again."

    old "Would I have done that if I hated you?"
    new "Would I have done that if I hated you?"

    old "Sarah felt a tear run past her face."
    new "Sarah felt a tear run past her face."

    old "I've...done more. Worse."
    new "I've...done more. Worse."

    old "Her heart was bursting. She didn't deserve Samayra. She wanted to confess a lifetime of sins."
    new "Her heart was bursting. She didn't deserve Samayra. She wanted to confess a lifetime of sins."

    old "Make her understand how awful she was."
    new "Make her understand how awful she was."

    old "Samayra leaned down and kissed her again."
    new "Samayra leaned down and kissed her again."

    old "Tell me. Tell me all of it and I'll still be here."
    new "Tell me. Tell me all of it and I'll still be here."

    old "Sarah seized the girl in an embrace and buried her face into Samayra's chest."
    new "Sarah seized the girl in an embrace and buried her face into Samayra's chest."

    old "The tears came and fell from her face against Samayra's skin, and Sarah felt her body shake from the sobs."
    new "The tears came and fell from her face against Samayra's skin, and Sarah felt her body shake from the sobs."

    old "But there was none of the rejection that Sarah knew in her heart she deserved."
    new "But there was none of the rejection that Sarah knew in her heart she deserved."

    old "Instead, as she professed all she'd ever done wrong, she felt Samayra's arms wrap further around her and pull her in tighter."
    new "Instead, as she professed all she'd ever done wrong, she felt Samayra's arms wrap further around her and pull her in tighter."

    old "Nestled in her arms, one former princess confessed all of her life to another former princess."
    new "Nestled in her arms, one former princess confessed all of her life to another former princess."

    old "And Samayra softly whispered all the words Sarah longed to hear, but imagined herself unworthy of."
    new "And Samayra softly whispered all the words Sarah longed to hear, but imagined herself unworthy of."

    old "Deep into the night, they kept to their embrace."
    new "Deep into the night, they kept to their embrace."

